FBIS4-53737 "dreas099_n_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 Vietnam U.S., Local Veterans Hold Meeting 17 May U.S., Local Veterans Hold Meeting 17 May BK2005122394 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 20 May 94 BK2005122394 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam English BFN [Text] The delegation of Vietnam Veterans of America led by Chairman James (?Brazier) arrived in Hanoi on Monday for an eight-day visit to Vietnam. The visit is to exchange information on soldiers reported missing from both United States and Vietnam. On 17 May the U.S. delegation had a working session with the leaders of the Vietnam War Veterans Association. Speaking with newsmen afterward, Mr. (Brazier) acknowledged that so far Vietnam has been very cooperative with the United States in solving the MIA issue. He said the United States of America was duly bound to respond to Vietnam's cooperation. The delegation of Vietnam Veterans of America also had a working session with the Foreign Ministry, the Ministry of Labor, Social, and War Invalids, the Vietnam-America Association, and the American Missing in Action Office in Vietnam. The delegation will call at Hue, Danang, Ho Chi Minh City, and other provinces.
